p: The third dominant group in feijoa essential oil composition was alcohol ( Figure 3). Besides the aforementioned alcohol compound α-cadinol (No. 111), linalool, espatulenol, rosifoliol, and (−)-spathulenol (No. 28, 101, 105, and 108, respectively) were also observed at high concentrations ( Figure 4), which is generally consistent with the former research [ 28]. However, alcohols were not determined as major volatile compounds in feijoa fruits [ 16, 32, 33], which suggested that these compounds may not be abundant in feijoa fruits, but were concentrated during the essential oil extraction.
